{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-09-25--Turning-monitor-mode-on-and-off/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Joel's dev blog","author":"Joel Mun","siteUrl":"https://9oelm.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7eb9a912-9b1f-5f80-86cd-3b915faef2e3","excerpt":"On This would just work: This also works: To scout the nearby APs, you do: Off For my computer, I do not have to type . It just works.  For more see theâ€¦","html":"<h2 id=\"on\" style=\"position:relative;\">On<a href=\"#on\" aria-label=\"on permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>This would just work:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">airmon-ng start wlan0</code></pre></div>\n<p>This also works:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ifconfig wlan0 down\niwconfig wlan0 mode monitor\nifconfig wlan0 up</code></pre></div>\n<p>To scout the nearby APs, you do:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">airodump-ng wlan0mon (or whatever the name ifconfig gives)</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"off\" style=\"position:relative;\">Off<a href=\"#off\" aria-label=\"off permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">~# airmon-ng stop wlan0mon\nPHY\tInterface\tDriver\t\tChipset\n\nphy0\twlan0mon\tath9k_htc\tAtheros Communications, Inc. AR9271 802.11n\n\t\t(mac80211 station mode vif enabled on [phy0]wlan0)\n\t\t(mac80211 monitor mode vif disabled for [phy0]wlan0mon)\n~# service network-manager start</code></pre></div>\n<p>For my computer, I do not have to type <code class=\"language-text\">service network-manager start</code>. It just works. </p>\n<h2 id=\"for-more\" style=\"position:relative;\">For more<a href=\"#for-more\" aria-label=\"for more permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>see <a href=\"https://www.aircrack-ng.org/doku.php?id=airmon-ng\">the official documentation</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Turning monitor mode on and off","date":"September 25, 2017","keywords":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2017-09-25--Turning-monitor-mode-on-and-off/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-25--Configuring-and-using-vim/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Configuring and using vim","tab":"post","tags":["linux","vim"],"keywords":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-28--Using-bluetooth-on-kali-linux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using bluetooth on kali linux","tab":"post","tags":["linux","kali"],"keywords":null}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3128451518","426816048"]}